]], has picked up the third series beginning on 3 June 2018.<ref>http://www.channel4.com/programmes/gogglebox-australia</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=4437104}}\n\n{{Network Ten programming}}\n\n[[Category:LifeStyle shows]]\n[[Category:Network 10 shows]]\n[[Category:Australian reality television series]]\n[[Category:2015 Australian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s Australian television series]]\n[[Category:Television series about television]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by Endemol]]\n[[Category:Australian television series based on British television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Australian reality television series}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Gogglebox Australia\n| genre                = Reality Television\n| based_on             = \n| caption              =\n| image                = Gogglebox_Australia_Title_Card.jpeg\n| num_seasons          = 11\n| num_episodes         = 99 <small>(as of 15 April 2020)</small>\n| list_episodes        = List of Gogglebox Australia episodes\n| director             =\n| presenter            = \n| judges               =\n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme            = \n| narrated             = Jo Van Es\n| country              = Australia\n| language             = English\n| producer             = \n| location             = [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] and [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]]\n| runtime              = 50 minutes\n| company              = [[Endemol Shine Australia|Shine Australia]]\n| network              = [[Network Ten]] (free-to-air)<br>[[LifeStyle]] (Pay TV)\n| picture_format       = 1080i (HDTV) \n| audio_format         = Stereo\n| first_run            = \n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2015|02|11|df=y}}\n| last_aired           = present \n| preceded_by          = \n| followed_by          = \n| website              = http://tenplay.com.au/channel-ten/gogglebox\n| website_title        = Official website ([[Network Ten#10 Play|10 Play]])\n| production_website   = http://www.lifestyle.com.au/gogglebox/\n| production_website_title = Official website (The LifeStyle Channel)\n}}\n\n'''''Gogglebox Australia''''' is an Australian [[reality television]] program. It is an adaptation of [[Gogglebox|the British series of the same name]]. The series, which is produced by [[Shine Australia]],<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2014/10/gogglebox-coming-to-foxtel.html|title=Gogglebox coming to Foxtel|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=23 August 2015}}</ref> is a co-production between subscription television (STV) channel [[Lifestyle (Australian TV channel)|Lifestyle]] (owned by [[Foxtel]]) and free-to-air (FTA) network [[Network Ten]].<ref name=\"Co-production\">{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2014/10/gogglebox-to-premiere-on-foxtel-one-night-ten-the-next.html|title=Gogglebox to premiere on Foxtel one night, TEN the next|date=30 October 2014|accessdate=23 August 2015}}</ref> It airs on Lifestyle first, and then airs on Network Ten a day later.<ref name=\"Co-production\"/>\n\n==Production==\nThe concept of ''Gogglebox Australia'' is based on the 2013 British reality show ''[[Gogglebox]]'', in which people watch and comment on the week's popular television shows and films in their own homes.<ref name=\"Kalina\">{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/tv-and-radio/gogglebox-australia-heres-what-it-is-and-why-you-would-watch-20150202-133x71.html|title=Gogglebox Australia: Here's what it is and why you would watch|last=Kalina|first=Paul|date=3 February 2015|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref> Producers chose ten households, featuring \"a cross-section of modern Australian society, from larrikins to gays, from migrant families to battlers, yuppies and empty-nesters\", to discuss the shows.<ref name=\"Kalina\"/> The cast are filmed with remote-controlled cameras, while the crew stay out of their way in other parts of the house.<ref name=\"Kalina\"/>\n\nVoiceover artist Jo Van Es narrates the series. She initially had doubts that she would secure the role following her audition, and thought it would be a short contract.<ref name=\"Voice\">{{cite web|url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2018/10/meet-the-voice-of-gogglebox.html|title=Meet the voice of Gogglebox|last=Knox|first=David|date=23 October 2018|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref> Van Es read a sample of the script without viewing the footage, which she described as \"a little bit tricky\", and she was told to give a largely neutral delivery.<ref name=\"Voice\"/> She said, \"I thought, 'This is a weird concept for a show. It will probably be something I do for a little while and it will disappear into the winds like a lot of jobs do.' But it's just grown and grown.\"<ref name=\"Voice\"/> Van Es starts her recordings during Tuesday afternoons and the sessions last for around an hour. When footage of a certain scene is not available to view, the writers and producers explain to Van Es how the tone of the narration should be and what words to emphasise.<ref name=\"Voice\"/> Over the seasons, Van Es's delivery has added more sass compared to the \"straight\" narration style of the early seasons.<ref name=\"Voice\"/>\n\nTen episodes of ''Gogglebox Australia'' were initially commissioned.<ref name=\"Kalina\"/> The first season aired on The LifeStyle Channel (later rebranded Lifestyle) and Network Ten between February and April 2015. At the conclusion of its debut season, the series was renewed for a second season,<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://tvtonight.com.au/2015/04/renewed-gogglebox-australia.html|title=Renewed: Gogglebox Australia|date=15 April 2014|accessdate=23 August 2015}}</ref> which premiered on STV on 30 September 2015, and on FTA on 1 October 2015.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/08/returning-gogglebox.html|title=Returning: Gogglebox Australia|date=30 August 2015|accessdate=30 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 September 2015, the series was renewed for a third season;<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/09/renewed-gogglebox-for-a-third-season.html|title=Renewed: Gogglebox (for a third season)|date=21 September 2015|accessdate=29 September 2015}}</ref> which premiered on STV on 6 April 2016, and on FTA on 7 April 2016.<ref name=\"S3\">{{cite web|last=Knox|first=David|title=Returning: Gogglebox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/03/returning-gogglebox-2.html|work=TV Tonight|date=14 March 2016|accessdate=14 March 2016}}</ref> On 8 February 2016, it was announced a fourth season had been commissioned;<ref>{{cite web|last=Knox|first=David|title=Programmer's Wrap 2016: Foxtel|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/02/programmers-wrap-2016-foxtel.html|work=TV Tonight|date=8 February 2016|accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref> which premiered on STV on 24 August 2016, and on FTA on 25 August 2016.<ref name=\"S4dates\">{{cite web|last=Knox|first=David|title=Returning: Gogglebox S4|url=http://tvtonight.com.au/2016/07/returning-gogglebox-3.html|work=TV Tonight|date=28 July 2016|accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 November 2016, the series was renewed for a fifth season, which premiered on 15 February 2017.<ref name=\"S5\">{{cite web|last=Knox|first=David|title=2017 Upfronts: TEN highlights|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/11/2017-upfronts-ten-highlights.html|work=TV Tonight|date=4 November 2016|accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Byrnes|first1=Holly|title=Gogglebox favourites Wayne andTom to introduce new family member Brandy Snaps to fans|url=http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/television/gogglebox-favourites-wayne-andtom-to-introduce-new-family-member-brandy-snaps-to-fans/news-story/fa61c15471ffb7db61b65cde2aea6186|accessdate=21 January 2017|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=21 January 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"S5airdate\">{{cite news|last1=Knox|first1=David|title=Returning: Gogglebox S5|url=http://tvtonight.com.au/2017/01/returning-gogglebox-4.html|accessdate=24 January 2017|work=TV Tonight|date=24 January 2017}}</ref> The series was later renewed for a sixth season, which premiered on 4 October 2017.<ref name=\"S6 airdate\">{{cite news|last1=Knox|first1=David|title=Returning: Gogglebox S6|url=http://tvtonight.com.au/2017/09/returning-gogglebox-5.html|accessdate=6 September 2017|work=TV Tonight|date=6 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017, Foxtel announced that the series was renewed for two further seasons to air in 2018, with each season to increase from eight to 10 episodes.<ref name=\"RenewS7&8\">{{cite news|title=Gogglebox Australia: Two new seasons confirmed for 2018|url=https://www.foxtel.com.au/whats-on/foxtel-insider/lifestyle/gogglebox-australia/gogglebox-accounce-two-more-seasons.html|accessdate=16 November 2017|work=Foxtel|date=9 November 2017}}</ref> The ninth season premiered on 6 February 2019.<ref name=\"Season9Premiere\">https://www.who.com.au/foxtel-announces-gogglebox-australia-season-9-premiere-date</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n\n===Current===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Viewers !! Duration !! About (Information)\n|-\n| '''Anastasia and Faye''' || Season 1\u2013 || Both born in Melbourne to Greek parents. \n|-\n| '''The Dalton family''' || Season 1\u2013 || Parents Matt, Kate, and their two daughters, Holly and Millie\n|-\n| '''The Delpechitra family''' || Season 1\u2013 || Parents Patrick and Tracey, sons Wendel and Ethan, daughter Vestal. Patrick and Tracey moved from Sri Lanka to Australia 25 years ago and live in Sydney's west.\n|-\n| '''Keith and Lee''' || Season 1\u2013 || With two grown-up children, the pair have celebrated 30 years of marriage and live in an outer-northern suburb of Melbourne.\n|-\n| '''Mick and Di''' || Season 1\u2013 || Indigenous art dealers who have been happily married for nearly 50 years, live in inner-city Sydney. \n|-\n| '''The Silbery family''' || Season 3\u2013 || Three generations of women \u2013 great grandma Emily, mum Kerry, and daughter Isabelle \u2013 based in Melbourne.\n|-\n| '''Matty, Sarah Marie and Jad''' || Season 6\u2013 || Lebanese Australians Matty, his wife Sarah Marie, and best friend Jad are from Sydney.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/sydney-confidential/gogglebox-sydney-trio-return-to-our-screens-with-a-new-british-bulldog-named-bane/news-story/66fcf0939bfb806e24b3f5ff6f89eb46|title=Gogglebox: Sydney trio return to our screens with a new British bulldog named Bane|last=Rutherford|first=Karlie|date=6 February 2018|work=[[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)|The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=6 February 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Tim and Leanne''' || Season 9\u2013 || Tim and Leanne are siblings from Melbourne.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newidea.com.au/gogglebox-new-cast-members-tim-leanne|title=Meet Gogglebox's newest cast members... Tim and Leanne|last=Tse|first=Liz|date=3 February 2019|work=[[New Idea]]|accessdate=3 February 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Milo and Nic''' || Season 11\u2013 || Best mates and flatmates, Milo and Nic met whilst working in a retail surf store over a decade ago on the Gold Coast.<ref name=S11families>{{cite web|url=https://tvblackbox.com.au/page/2020/2/13/gogglebox-australia-welcomes-three-new-households?format=non-amp|title=GOGGLEBOX AUSTRALIA Welcomes Three New Households|date=13 February 2020|work=TV Blackbox|accessdate=13 February 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Kaday and Chantel''' || Season 11\u2013 || Kaday and Chantel met while hanging washing in their shared Sydney Eastern suburbs apartment building.<ref name=\"S11families\" />\n|-\n| '''The Elias Family''' || Season 11\u2013 || Parents Les and Danielle, eldest son Jacob, daughter Lily Rose and youngest daughter Ivy from the suburbs of Sydney.<ref name=\"S11families\" />\n|-\n|}\n\n===Former===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Viewers !! Duration !! About (Information)\n|-\n| '''The Jackson family''' || Season 1\u201310 || Parents Stacey and Grant and their six children Corey, Britney, Jesse, Chase, Kane and Nate from Penrith, in western Sydney.\n|-\n| '''Symon and Adam''' || Season 1\u201310 || Best mates and larrikins, the physiotherapy students met on a university pub crawl in Melbourne. In the season 3 premiere, it was announced Symon and Adam had graduated from university and begun their careers. Symon and Adam decided to quit the show at the end of season 10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heraldsun.com.au/entertainment/fiona-byrne/gossip-queen-serial-watchers-bid-goodbye-to-the-box/news-story/68484be270786e8723c331a4fccfb767|title=Gossip Queen: Serial watchers bid goodbye to the box|last=Byrne|first=Fiona|date=23 November 2019|work=Herald Sun|accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Angie and Yvie''' || Season 1\u20138 || The Sunshine Coast housemates whose place is bustling and chaotic thanks to the small circus of dogs they foster. Angie and Yvie chose to leave the show at the end of season 8 because Angie had left their house in Sydney and couldn't travel regularly to Sydney anymore.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nowtolove.com.au/celebrity/tv/gogglebox-angie-yvie-tom-wayne-quit-52952|title=Four of your favourite Gogglebox Australia stars just announced their departure from the show|last=Burke|first=Tina|date=7 December 2018|work=TV Week|accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.who.com.au/why-gogglebox-angie-kent-yvie-jones-quit|title=Why Gogglebox Angie Kent and Yvie Jones Quit|last=Lal|first=Chloe|date=10 December 2018|work=Who|accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://au.lifestyle.yahoo.com/gogglebox-stars-announced-newest-im-celeb-contestants-033635578.html?guccounter=1|title=Gogglebox stars announced as newest I'm A Celeb contestants|last=Velk|first=Eliza|date=7 January 2019|work=Yahoo! Lifestyle|accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Wayne and Tom''' || Season 1\u20138 || The Melbourne couple met at a country dance. They have raised three children together and are engaged. The couple and their dog, Satie, share the lounge together every night. In the season 2 premiere, it was revealed that Satie had died. Wayne and Tom quit the series at the end of season 8.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2018/10/wayne-tom-quitting-gogglebox.html|title=Wayne & Tom quitting Gogglebox|last=Knox|first=David|date=7 October 2018|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|accessdate=6 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''The Kidd family''' || Season 1\u20132 || Parents Stuart and Janet, son Michael, his wife Elena, and youngest son Roger from the Blue Mountains. They did not return for season 3 due to availability issues.<ref name=\"Season3\">{{cite web|last=Knox|first=David|title=Gogglebox casts new families|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2016/03/gogglebox-casts-new-families.html|work=TV Tonight|date=23 March 2016|accessdate=25 March 2016}}</ref>\nStuart died from suicide in May 2018. The season 8 premiere was dedicated to him.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.who.com.au/gogglebox-angie-yvie-tribute-to-stuart-kidd|title=Gogglebox: Angie and Yvie's tribute to the late Dr. Stuart Kidd|last=Price|first=Natasha|date=31 August 2018|work=[[Who (magazine)|Who]]|accessdate=26 September 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Zina and Vivian''' || Season 3\u20135 || Melburnian house-mates who have been friends since high school. They did not return for season 6 as Vivian had moved overseas and Zina was embarking on new adventures.<ref>{{cite web|last=Knox|first=David|title=Returning: Gogglebox|publisher=TV Tonight|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2017/09/returning-gogglebox-5.html|date=6 September 2017|accessdate=6 September 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Cast timeline===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width:\"50%\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Viewers !! colspan=11 style=text-align:center; | Seasons\n|-\n!! width=\"65\" | 1\n!! width=\"65\" | 2<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|title=Gogglebox: promo|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/09/gogglebox-promo.html|date=11 September 2015|accessdate=29 September 2015}}</ref>\n!! width=\"65\"| 3<ref name=\"Season3\"/>\n!! width=\"65\"| 4<ref name=\"S4dates\"/>\n!! width=\"65\"| 5<ref name=\"S5airdate\" />\n!! width=\"65\"| 6<ref name=\"S6 airdate\" />\n!! width=\"65\"| 7\n!! width=\"65\"| 8\n!! width=\"65\"| 9\n!! width=\"65\"| 10\n!! width=\"65\"| 11\n|-\n| Symon Lovett & Adam Densten || colspan=\"10\" {{yes2}} || colspan=\"1\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| Anastasia Katselas & Faye Kontos || colspan=\"3\" {{yes2}} || {{yes2}} {{refn|Faye was absent for episode 1 and 2 of season 4 as she was on holiday. Anastasia was joined by her mother Angela in Faye's absence.|group=note}} || colspan=\"7\" {{yes2}} \n|-\n| Mick & Di Kershaw || colspan=\"3\" {{yes2}} || {{yes2}}{{refn|Mick & Di were absent in episodes 6 and 7 of season 4 as they were on holiday in Italy.season 11 absent from 5 episodes to end of filming due to Covid 19|group=note}} || colspan=\"7\" {{yes2}}\n|-\n| Keith & Lee Lee || {{yes2}} || {{yes2}}{{refn|Lee & Keith were absent for episode 4 and 5 of season 2 as they were on holiday for their 30th wedding anniversary.|group=note}} || colspan=\"9\" {{yes2}} \n|-\n| The Dalton family || colspan=\"11\" {{yes2}}\n|-\n| The Delpechitra family || colspan=\"11\" {{yes2}}\n|-\n| The Jackson family || colspan=\"10\" {{yes2}} || colspan=\"1\" {{n/a|}}\n|-\n| [[Angie Kent]] & [[Yvie Jones]] || colspan=\"5\" {{yes2}} ||{{yes2}} {{refn|Angie & Yvie were absent for episode 6 of season 6 due to illness.|group=note}} || {{yes2}} || {{yes2}} {{refn|Angie & Yvie w