erica Punishment and Inequality in America].'' [[Russell Sage Foundation]]. {{ISBN|087154895X}}\n* DeConde, A. (2001). Gun Violence in America. 1st ed. Boston: [[Northeastern University Press]].\n*{{cite book |author1=Todd R. Clear|author2=Natasha A. Frost|title=The Punishment Imperative: The Rise and Failure of Mass Incarceration in America|isbn=978-1479851690|year=2015|publisher=NYU Press}}\n\n===Articles and interviews===\n* [http://www.truthdig.com/report/item/the_prison_state_of_america_20141228 The Prison State of America] (2014-12-28), [[Chris Hedges]], ''[[Truthdig]]''\n* [http://therealnews.com/t2/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=31&Itemid=74&jumival=12928 How Prisons Rip Off and Exploit the Incarcerated, Part I] (2015-01-04) and [http://therealnews.com/t2/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=31&Itemid=74&jumival=12929 Part II] (2015-01-07), [[Marshall \"Eddie\" Conway]] and [[Chris Hedges]], ''[[The Real News]]''\n* [http://therealnews.com/t2/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=31&Itemid=74&jumival=12885 Do Prisons and Mass Incarceration Keep Us Safe? Part I] (2015-01-11) and [http://therealnews.com/t2/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=31&Itemid=74&jumival=12925 Part II] (2015-01-13), [[Marshall \"Eddie\" Conway]] and Maya Schenwar, author of ''Locked Down and Locked Out.''  ''[[The Real News]].'' &nbsp;  &nbsp; See also  [http://www.tomdispatch.com/post/175944/tomgram%3A_maya_schenwar%2C_prison_by_any_other_name/ Tomgram: Maya Schenwar, Prison by Any Other Name] (2015-01-18), ''[[Tom Engelhardt|TomDispatch]]''\n* [http://www.truth-out.org/news/item/29095-carceral-conglomerate-makes-millions-from-incarcerated-their-friends-and-families# \"Carceral Conglomerate\" Makes Millions From Incarcerated, Their Friends and Families] (February 2015), [[Symbionese Liberation Army|James Kilgore]] and Brian Dolinar, ''[[Truthout]]''\n* [http://www.truth-out.org/news/item/8731 Prison Industries: \"Don't Let Society Improve or We Lose Business\