ology-series-in-works-at-syfy-from-jeff-davis-david-janollari-1202514957/amp/|title=\u2018Night Gallery\u2019: Reimagining Of Rod Serling\u2019s Anthology Series In Works At Syfy From Jeff Davis & David Janollari|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=December 6, 2018|accessdate=June 12, 2019}}</ref>\n*''[[The Woods (comic)#Television adaptation|The Woods]]\n\n==Past programs==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc;\"\n! Series\n! Debut\n! End\n! Studio\n! Genre\n! Notes\n|-\n|''[[12 Monkeys (TV series)|12 Monkeys]]''\n|{{dts|2015-01-16}}\n|{{dts|2018-07-06}}\n|Division Street, [[Atlas Entertainment]], [[Universal Cable Productions]]\n|Drama, Mystery, Science fiction\n|Loose adaption of the [[12 Monkeys|1995 film of the same name]] which in turn was inspired by the short film ''[[La Jet\u00e9e]]''.\n|-\n|''[[Aftermath (2016 TV series)|Aftermath]]''\n|{{dts|2016-09-27}}\n|{{dts|2016-12-20}}\n|[[Bell Media]], Universal Cable Productions, Halfire Entertainment\n|Drama, Science fiction\n|Imported from Canadian channel [[Space (Canadian TV channel)|Space]]. The series is centered on the Copeland family, a couple with three almost-grown children, who struggle to survive as natural disasters, followed by the rise of supernatural beings, brings civilization to an end. Cancelled after one season.\n|-\n|''[[Alphas]]''\n|{{dts|2011-07-11}}\n|{{dts|2012-10-22}}\n|[[BermanBraun]], Universal Cable Productions\n|[[Action (genre)|Action]]/Adventure, Drama, [[Science fantasy]], Science fiction\n|A group of people with superhuman abilities, known as \"Alphas\", work to prevent crimes committed by other Alphas. Cancelled after number of viewers decreased.<ref name=AlphasEnd>{{cite news|title=Alphas cancelled|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/syfy-cancels-alphas-413099|accessdate=May 30, 2013 | work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Philiana|last=Ng}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[The Almighty Johnsons]]''\n|{{dts|2014-07-11}}\n|{{dts|2014}}\n|South Pacific Pictures\n|Fantasy, comedy-drama\n|Imported from New Zealand channel TV3. All three seasons were originally going to air but the first two seasons were broadcast instead.\n|-\n|''[[Andromeda (TV series)|Andromeda]]''\n|{{dts|2000-10-02}}\n|{{dts|2005-05-13}}\n|[[Tribune Entertainment]]\n|[[Space opera]]\n|First four years were syndication-only.\n|-\n|''[[Battlestar Galactica (2004 TV series)|Battlestar Galactica]]''\n|{{dts|2003-12-08}}\n|{{dts|2009-03-20}}\n|David Eick Productions<br />R&D TV<br />[[Universal Television]]<br />Universal Media Studios<br />[[Universal Cable Productions]]\n|Space opera\n|Reimagining of the [[Battlestar Galactica (1978 TV series)|1978 television series of the same name]]. The 2003 [[Battlestar Galactica (TV miniseries)|miniseries]] served as a backdoor pilot.\n|-\n|''Bazillion Dollar Club''\n|{{dts|2015-09-22}}\n|{{dts|2015-09-22}}\n|Zero Point Zero\n|Reality\n|Originally going to air six episodes, Syfy pulled the show after the first episode premiered.\n|-\n|''[[Beast Legends]]''\n|{{dts|2010-09-09}}\n|{{dts|2010-10-14}}\n|Yap Films\n|Documentary, Reality, Paranormal, Mystery, Thriller, Adventure, Outdoors\n|\n|-\n|''[[Being Human (North American TV series)|Being Human]]''\n|{{dts|2011-01-17}}\n|{{dts|2014-04-07}}\n|[[Muse Entertainment|Muse Entertainment Enterprises]], [[Zodiak Entertainment]], Universal Cable Worldwide Sales and Distribution\n|[[Supernatural]], [[Comedy-drama]], [[Horror and terror|Horror]]\n|Based on the UK TV series of the [[Being Human (UK TV series)|same name]]. The series was cancelled at the time the remaining episodes of season four were airing.\n|-\n|''[[Bitten (TV series)|Bitten]]''\n|{{dts|2014-01-13}}\n|{{dts|2016-04-25}}\n|[[Entertainment One]], [[Entertainment One Television]], No Equal Entertainment, Hoodwink Entertainment, [[Bell Media]]\n|Drama, Horror, Fantasy\n|Imported from Canadian channel Space. Based on the ''[[Women of the Otherworld]]'' series by [[Kelley Armstrong]] in addition