oy Meets Girl Film Company, [[Shaw Media]], GK-TV\n|Drama, Action, Science Fiction\n|Imported from Canadian channel [[Showcase (Canadian TV channel)|Showcase]].\n|-\n|''[[Dark Matter (TV series)|Dark Matter]]''\n|{{dts|2015-06-12}}\n|{{dts|2017-08-25}}\n|Prodigy Pictures Inc., [[Dark Horse Entertainment]]\n|[[Space opera]]\n|Imported from Canadian channel Space. Based on the [[Dark Matter (comics)|comic book series of the same name]]. Cancelled after three seasons.\n|-\n|''[[Deadly Class (TV series)|Deadly Class]]''\n|{{dts|2019-01-16}}\n|{{dts|2019-03-20}}\n|Gozie AGBO, Chipmunk Hill, Getaway Productions, Giant Generator, 2 Miles Entertainment, [[Universal Cable Productions]], [[Universal Content Productions|Sony Pictures Television]]\n|[[Action film|Action]], [[Adventure]], [[Black comedy]], [[Drama film|Drama]], [[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]\n|\n|-\n|''Deals from the Darkside''\n|{{dts|2012-11-07}}\n|{{dts|2012-12-12}}\n|Buck Productions\n|[[Reality television]], [[Documentary]]\n|Reality show centered around the history of various items and their connections to tragic or mysterious events.\n|-\n|''[[Deep South Paranormal]]''\n|{{dts|2013-04-10}}\n|{{dts|2013-05-15}}\n|Thunder Road Productions\n|Paranormal\n|A group of ghost hunters from the deep south follow their paranormal investigations to different reportedly haunted locations in the Southern United States. Cancelled after one season.\n|-\n|''[[Defiance (TV series)|Defiance]]''\n|{{dts|2013-04-15}}\n|{{dts|2015-08-28}}\n|Five & Dime Productions, [[Universal Cable Productions]], [[NBC Universal Television]], Syfy\n|Science fiction\n|Transmedia collaboration between Universal Cable productions and [[Trion Worlds]], who have released an [[Massively multiplayer online game|MMORPG]] video game [[Defiance (video game)|of the same name]] which is tied into the series. The series was originally cancelled due to a financial decision but the video game companion's patch continued the story line as season four.\n|-\n|'