ot fighting competition hosted by [[Chris Jericho]].\n|-\n|''[[Sanctuary (TV series)|Sanctuary]]''\n|{{dts|2008-10-03}}\n|{{dts|2011-12-30}}\n|\n|Sci-fi, [[Fantasy]]\n|A doctor and her team study and protect the strange creatures living in their world. First North American series to be filmed with [[Red Digital Cinema Camera Company|Red One camera]]. Cancelled six months after the season four finale aired.\n|-\n|''[[Scare Tactics]]''\n|{{dts|2013-04}}\n|{{dts|2013-10-28}}\n|\n|Hidden camera, Comedy\n|\n|-\n|''[[School Spirits]]''\n|{{dts|2012-06-22}}\n|{{dts|2012-08-01}}\n|Realand Productions, Jarrett Creative\n|[[Paranormal]], [[Documentary]]\n|Series where accounts of paranormal activity in schools and universities are told through reenactments.\n|-\n|''[[The Secret Adventures of Jules Verne]]''\n|{{dts|2000-06-18}}\n|{{dts|2000-12-16}}\n|Filmline International Inc., Talisman Crest\n|[[Steampunk]]\n|The untold adventures of the famed writer and his friends. First series filmed entirely in [[HDTV]] format.\n|-\n|''[[Sightings (TV series)|Sightings]]''\n|{{dts|1996}}\n|{{dts|1998}}\n|Ann Daniels Productions, Fair Dinkum Productions, [[Paramount Television]]\n|[[Reality television]], [[Paranormal]]\n|A paranormal news show from the early 1990s.\n|-\n|''[[Sinbad (TV series)|Sinbad]]''\n|{{dts|2013-06-08}}\n|{{dts|2013-08-03}}\n|Impossible Pictures<br />BBC Worldwide, BSkyB\n|Fantasy, Adventure\n|Imported from United Kingdom channel [[Sky1]]. Originally going to air all the episodes weekly but Syfy burned off the final episodes in one day.\n|-\n|''[[Sliders]]''\n|{{dts|1998-06-06}}\n|{{dts|2000-02-04}}\n|[[St. Clare Entertainment]], [[Studios USA Television]], [[Universal TV]]\n|Sci-fi, Dimensional travel\n|A [[Fox Network|FOX]] original series for the first three seasons, but the fourth and fifth seasons were produced for Syfy.\n|-\n|''[[Stargate SG-1]]''\n|{{dts|2002}}\n|{{dts|2007-03-13}}\n|MGM\n|[[Military science fiction]], [[Wormholes in fiction|Wormhole]]\n|[[Sh