ality competition show\n|Teams of magicians create and perform original magic routines before a live studio audience\n|-\n|''[[WWE NXT (TV series)|WWE NXT]]''\n|{{dts|2010-02-23}}\n|{{dts|2010-09-28}}\n|WWE\n|Professional wrestling\n|A group of rookies get paired with their pros as they fight for a chance to earn a future title shot. The series was moved to online after Syfy picked up sister series ''WWE Smackdown''.\n|-\n|''[[WWE SmackDown]]''\n|{{dts|2010-10-01}}\n|{{dts|2015-12-31}}\n|WWE\n|Professional wrestling\n|Was picked up in favor of ''WWE NXT'' after WWE signed a multi-year agreement with the network until the show moved to Syfy's sister channel [[USA Network]] in early 2016.\n|-\n|''[[Z Nation]]''\n|{{dts|2014-9-10}}\n|{{dts|2018-12-28}}\n|[[The Asylum]]<br>Go2 Digital Media<br>North By Northwest\n|Action, Horror, Comedy-drama, [[Post-apocalypse]]\n|Three years after the Zombie virus has gutted the United States of America, a team of everyday heroes must transport the only known survivor of the plague from New York to California, where the last functioning viral lab for his blood.\n|}\n\n==Syfy second-run programming==<!-- This section is linked from [[List of science fiction television programs]] -->\nSyfy has a long history of buying the rights to air second-run or repeat programming of series no longer in production.\n\n===Current programs===\n* ''[[The Twilight Zone (1959 TV series)|The Twilight Zone]]'' (1995\u2013present)\n* ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'' (2014\u2013present)\n* ''[[Futurama]]'' (2017\u2013present){{refn|group=note|name=tzgz1|Also airs in TZGZ block.}}\n* ''[[Gary and His Demons]]'' (2019\u2013present){{refn|group=note|name=tzgz2|Also airs in TZGZ block.}}\n* ''[[NCIS: Los Angeles]]'' (2020\u2013present)\n\n===Past programs===\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* ''[[The 4400]]''\n* ''[[Alfred Hitchcock Presents (1985 TV series)|Alfred Hitchcock Presents]]''\n* ''[[Alien Nation (TV series)|Alien Nation]]''\n* ''[[All Souls (TV seri