 runaway ferris wheel and fixing it, The Thing is offered a job at the carnival by its owner.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 8\n| Title               = The Thing Blanks Out\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|9|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = Benjy and his friends enjoy a trip aboard Ronald's father's yacht; Thing saves the group from crashing into a downed drawbridge, but then he is stricken with amnesia following the closing drawbridge's impact on his head.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 9\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 9\n| Title               = The Thing Meets the Clunk\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dr. Quimby introduces his latest invention \u2013 a robot called Clunk who is programmed to do good \u2013 however, the robot malfunctions, goes out-of-control and causes trouble for The Thing.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 10\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 10\n| Title               = Beach Party Crashers\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = Benjy attends a beachside surf party with Kelly, Betty, Ronald and Miss Twilly, but the Yancy Street Gang are up to their old tricks as they crash the party and sabotage a volleyball game.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 11\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 11\n| Title               = Decepto the Great\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|13}}\n| ShortSummary        = A magician, Decepto the Great, performs his magic show at the high school fair, but Benjy discovers Decepto is stealing from the school kids and it's up to The Thing to stop him from escaping town.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 12\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 12\n| Title               = The Thing's the Play\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|13}}\n| ShortSummary        = Betty studies with acting teacher Ferdinand Bestmore so she can audition for a TV crew coming to Centerville High School to shoot a commercial; however, Bestmore confuses Betty with an old actress he once discovered and whom she resembles so he kidnaps her.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 13\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 13\n| Title               = Double Trouble for the Thing\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|20}}\n| ShortSummary        = An evil scientist named Danton Blackwood creates a robot Thing to commit crime to make the citizens believe The Thing has gone bad, but which also lands the real Thing in jail.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 14\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 14\n| Title               = To Thing or Not to Thing\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|20}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 15\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 15\n| Title               = The Big Bike Race\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|27}}\n| ShortSummary        = Benjy enters a cross country bike race because the winner gets to escort the Race Queen to the dance.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 16\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 16\n| Title               = The Thing and the Treasure Hunt\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|10|27}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 17\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 17\n| Title               = Out to Launch\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1979|11|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Benjy and his friends are going to a ship launching but the world's greatest demolition expert intends to ruin the day.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 18\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 18\n| Title           